'''Sead Kolašinac''' ({{IPA|bs|sěad kolaʃîːnats|pron}}; born 20 June 1993) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] for [[Serie A]] club [[Atalanta BC|Atalanta]]. Born in Germany, he plays for the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina national team]].

Kolašinac started his professional career at [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]], playing first in its [[FC Schalke 04 II|reserve team]], before joining [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in 2017, who loaned him back to Schalke 04 in 2021. The following year, he moved to [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]]. A year later, he signed with Atalanta.

A former German youth international, Kolašinac made his senior international debut for Bosnia and Herzegovina in 2013, earning over 60 [[Cap (sport)|caps]] since. He represented the nation at their first ever major championship, the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]].

==Club career==

===Schalke 04===
[[File:Sead Kolašinac S04 2015 (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|Kolašinac with [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]] in 2015]]

Kolašinac started playing football at his hometown club [[Karlsruher SC]], which he joined in 2001. In 2009, he moved to [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|TSG Hoffenheim's youth academy]]. A year later, he switched to [[VfB Stuttgart|VfB Stuttgart's youth setup]]. In 2011, he went to [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04's youth academy]]. In June 2012, he signed his first professional contract with the team.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://kicker.de/simeone-hofft-auf-diego-de-wit-bleibt-in-lautern-569894/artikel|title=Simeone hofft auf Diego, de Wit bleibt in Lautern|website=kicker.de|date=1 June 2012|access-date=1 June 2012|language=de}}</ref> He made his professional debut against [[SpVgg Greuther Fürth|Greuther Fürth]] on 15 September at the age of 19.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://kicker.de/fuerth-gegen-schalke-2012-bundesliga-1441668/analyse|title=Holtby nimmt Fürth endgültig den Mut|website=kicker.de|date=15 September 2012|access-date=17 September 2012|language=de}}</ref>

Kolašinac debuted in the [[2012–13 UEFA Champions League#Group B|UEFA Champions League]] away at [[Montpellier HSC|Montpellier]] on 4 December.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://kicker.de/montpellier-gegen-schalke-2012-champions-league-1844962/analyse|title=Herrera bezwingt Hildebrand nur einmal|website=kicker.de|date=4 December 2012|access-date=7 December 2012|language=de}}</ref>

In June 2013, he extended his deal with the squad until June 2017.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/sead-kolasinac-produzio-ugovor-sa-schalkeom/107796|title=Sead Kolašinac produžio ugovor sa Schalkeom|website=sportsport.ba|date=25 June 2013|access-date=27 June 2013|language=bs}}</ref>

In August 2014, he suffered a severe knee injury, which was diagnosed as an [[Anterior cruciate ligament injury|anterior cruciate ligament tear]] and was ruled out for at least six months. Over seven months after the injury, on 11 April 2015, he returned to the pitch.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/23100-povratak-u-velikom-stilu-kolasinac-pun-samopouzdanja-ponovo-zaigrao-za-schalke|title=Povratak u velikom stilu: Kolašinac pun samopouzdanja ponovo zaigrao za Schalke|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=11 April 2015|access-date=12 April 2015|language=bs}}</ref>

On 13 December, he scored his first professional goal against [[FC Augsburg]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/kolasinac-sjajno-pogodio-schalke-ipak-porazen/178604|title=Kolašinac sjajno pogodio, Schalke ipak poražen|website=sportsport.ba|date=13 December 2015|access-date=13 December 2015|language=bs}}</ref>

He played his 100th game for the club on 3 December 2016 against [[RB Leipzig]], managed to score a goal and an own goal.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/leipzig-pobijedio-i-schalke-kolasinac-u-100-nastupu-za-klub-postigao-gol-i-autogol/161203089|title=Leipzig pobijedio i Schalke, Kolašinac u 100. nastupu za klub postigao gol i autogol|website=klix.ba|date=3 December 2016|access-date=5 December 2016|language=bs}}</ref>

===Arsenal===
[[File:Kolasinac 2017.jpg|thumb|upright|Kolašinac playing for [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in 2017]]

In June 2017, Kolašinac signed a five-year contract with English side [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://fokus.ba/sport/fudbal/sead-kolasinac-i-zvanicno-novi-clan-arsenala/752219|title=Sead Kolašinac i zvanično novi član Arsenala|website=fokus.ba|date=6 June 2017|access-date=7 June 2017|language=bs}}</ref>

====2017–18 season====
He made his official debut for the club in the [[2017 FA Community Shield]] match against [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] on 6 August, scored a goal and won his first trophy.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/288608/arsenal-osvojio-svoj-prvi-trofej-ove-sezone-kolasinac-strijelac-na-debiju|title=Arsenal osvojio svoj prvi trofej ove sezone, Kolašinac strijelac na debiju|website=avaz.ba|date=6 August 2017|access-date=7 August 2017|language=bs}}</ref> A week later, he made his league debut against [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/spektakl-u-londonu-arsenal-do-pobjede-cudesnim-preokretom/247914|title=Spektakl u Londonu: Arsenal do pobjede čudesnim preokretom|website=sportsport.ba|date=11 August 2017|access-date=12 August 2017|language=bs}}</ref>

In September 2017, he was voted Arsenal's Player of the Month for August.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/kolasinac-izabran-za-najboljeg-igraca-arsenala-u-augustu/170905060|title=Kolašinac izabran za najboljeg igrača Arsenala u augustu|website=klix.ba|date=5 September 2017|access-date=7 September 2017|language=bs}}</ref>

On 28 October, he scored his first league goal for the squad in a triumph over [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea City]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/235370-sead-kolasinac-pogodio-i-asistirao-za-trijumf-arsenala|title=Sead Kolašinac pogodio i asistirao za trijumf Arsenala|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=28 October 2017|access-date=1 November 2017|language=bs}}</ref>

He was once again voted Arsenal's Player of the Month, this time for October.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/sead-opet-najbolji-kolasinac-drugi-put-proglasen-igracem-mjeseca/281580|title=Sead opet najbolji: Kolašinac drugi put proglašen igračem mjeseca|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=14 November 2017|access-date=17 November 2017|language=bs}}</ref>

====2018–19 season====
In August 2018, Kolašinac picked up a knee injury during a pre-season clash against Chelsea, which ruled him out for the start of the season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/402809/peh-kolasinac-zbog-povrede-propusta-pocetak-sezone|title=Peh: Kolašinac zbog povrede propušta početak sezone|website=avaz.ba|date=4 August 2018|access-date=7 August 2018|language=bs}}</ref> He made his season debut in a [[2018–19 UEFA Europa League#Group E|UEFA Europa League]] tie against [[Qarabağ FK|Qarabağ]] on 4 October.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/hajrovic-i-gojak-strijelci-u-pobjedi-dinama-vranjes-pocrvenio-kolasinac-se-vratio-na-teren/181004136|title=Hajrović i Gojak strijelci u pobjedi Dinama, Vranješ pocrvenio, Kolašinac se vratio na teren|website=klix.ba|date=4 October 2018|access-date=7 October 2018|language=bs}}</ref>

====2019–20 season====
Kolašinac played his first fixture of the campaign in a defeat of [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] on 17 August 2019.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/arsenal-bolji-od-burnelyja-zaigrao-i-sead-kolasinac/22020|title=Arsenal bolji od Burnelyja, zaigrao i Sead Kolašinac|website=faktor.ba|date=17 August 2019|access-date=17 August 2019|language=bs}}</ref>

On 15 July 2020, he made his 100th appearance for the side against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/581984/kolasinac-protiv-novog-prvaka-engleske-zabiljezio-vrijedan-jubilej|title=Kolašinac protiv novog prvaka Engleske zabilježio vrijedan jubilej|website=avaz.ba|date=16 July 2020|access-date=17 July 2020|language=bs}}</ref>

He won his first major piece of silverware with Arsenal on 1 August, by beating Chelsea in the [[2019–20 FA Cup|FA Cup]] final.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/sead-kolasinac-osvajanje-prvog-velikog-trofeja-u-karijeri-proslavio-sa-zastavom-bih/200801096|title=Sead Kolašinac osvajanje prvog velikog trofeja u karijeri proslavio sa zastavom BiH|website=klix.ba|date=1 August 2020|access-date=1 August 2020|language=bs}}</ref>

====2020–21 season====
Kolašinac debuted in the season in the [[2020 FA Community Shield]] tie against Liverpool on 29 August.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/arsenal-savladao-liverpool-i-stigao-do-prvog-trofeja-u-novoj-sezoni/388213|title=Arsenal savladao Liverpool i stigao do prvog trofeja u novoj sezoni|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=29 August 2020|access-date=1 September 2020|language=bs}}</ref>

In January 2021, he was sent on a six-month loan to his former club Schalke 04 and became its [[Captain (association football)|captain]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n1info.ba/sport/nogomet/kolasinac-se-vratio-u-schalke-postaje-kapiten|title=Kolašinac se vratio u Schalke, postaje kapiten|website=n1info.ba|date=2 January 2021|access-date=2 January 2021|language=bs}}</ref> He played his first competitive game for the team since coming back on 9 January against TSG Hoffenheim.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/622736/kolasinac-predvodio-schalke-do-prve-pobjede-u-sezoni|title=Kolašinac predvodio Schalke do prve pobjede u sezoni|website=avaz.ba|date=9 January 2021|access-date=12 January 2021|language=bs}}</ref> On 27 February, he scored first goal for Schalke 04 since his comeback in a loss to VfB Stuttgart.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/petarda-raspolozenog-bayerna-sigurna-borussija-i-nova-blamaza-schalkea/210227070|title=Petarda raspoloženog Bayerna, sigurna Borussija i nova blamaža Schalkea|website=klix.ba|date=27 February 2021|access-date=1 March 2021|language=bs}}</ref>

====2021–22 season====
Kolašinac appeared in his first match of the season in an [[2021–22 EFL Cup#Second round|EFL Cup]] fixture against [[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion]] on 25 August.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/333872-kolasinac-odigrao-cijeli-susret-arsenal-zabio-sest-golova|title=Kolašinac odigrao cijeli susret, Arsenal zabio šest golova|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=25 August 2021|access-date=27 August 2021|language=bs}}</ref>

In November, he suffered an ankle injury, which was diagnosed as a [[Ankle fracture|broken ankle]] and was expected to be sidelined for at least two months.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/arsenal-objavio-saopstenje-poznato-kada-se-vraca-sead-kolasinac/413134|title=Arsenal objavio saopštenje: Poznato kada se vraća Sead Kolašinac|website=sportsport.ba|date=26 November 2021|access-date=27 November 2021|language=bs}}</ref>

===Marseille===
[[File:Lens - Marseille (22-01-2022) 24.jpg|thumb|upright|Kolašinac with [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] in 2022]]

In January 2022, Kolašinac moved to French outfit [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] on a deal until June 2023.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/sead-kolasinac-novi-igrac-marseillea/112726|title=Sead Kolašinac novi igrač Marseillea|website=faktor.ba|date=18 January 2022|access-date=19 January 2022|language=bs}}</ref> He debuted officially for the squad on 4 February against [[Angers SCO|Angers]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n1info.ba/sport/nogomet/milik-sa-tri-gola-srusio-angers-kolasinac-igrao-sat-vremena-na-debiju|title=Milik sa tri gola srušio Angers, Kolašinac igrao sat vremena na debiju|website=n1info.ba|date=4 February 2022|access-date=7 February 2022|language=bs}}</ref> On 13 November, he scored his first goal for Marseille against [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]], which secured the victory for his team.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/375111-sead-kolasinac-u-98-minuti-postigao-gol-za-pobjedu-marseillea|title=Sead Kolašinac u 98. minuti postigao gol za pobjedu Marseillea|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=13 November 2022|access-date=14 November 2022|language=bs}}</ref>

===Atalanta===
In July 2023, Kolašinac joined Italian side [[Atalanta BC|Atalanta]] on a three-year contract.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://oslobodjenje.ba/sport/fudbal/ino-fudbal/serie-a/u-gradu-je-novi-tenk-atalanta-predstavila-seada-kolasinca-874578|title=U gradu je novi tenk: Atalanta predstavila Seada Kolašinca|website=oslobodjenje.ba|date=6 July 2023|access-date=7 July 2023|language=bs}}</ref> He debuted competitively for the outfit against [[US Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]] on 20 August.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/debitovao-kolasinac-atalanti-tri-gostujuca-boda-na-startu-sezone/164763|title=Debitovao Kolašinac, Atalanti tri gostujuća boda na startu sezone|website=faktor.ba|date=20 August 2023|access-date=23 August 2023|language=bs}}</ref> On 8 October, he scored his first goal for Atalanta against [[SS Lazio|Lazio]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/859945/golijada-u-rimu-kolasinac-postigao-prvijenac-za-atalantu|title=Golijada u Rimu, Kolašinac postigao prvijenac za Atalantu|website=avaz.ba|date=8 October 2023|access-date=10 October 2023|language=bs}}</ref> He won his first title with the club on 22 May 2024, by beating [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]] in the [[2023–24 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]] final.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://scsport.ba/medalja-za-kolasinca-hat-trick-lookmana-atalanta-nanijela-prvi-poraz-bayeru-ove-sezone-i-podigla-trofej-uefa-europa-lige|title=Medalja za Kolašinca, hat-trick Lookmana: Atalanta nanijela prvi poraz Bayeru ove sezone i podigla trofej UEFA Europa Lige|website=scsport.ba|date=22 May 2024|access-date=23 May 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

Kolašinac scored his first [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League#League phase|UEFA Champions League]] goal on 26 November against [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/kolasinac-postigao-prvijenac-u-ligi-prvaka-city-prokockao-tri-gola-prednosti/241126197|title=Kolašinac postigao prvijenac u Ligi prvaka, City prokockao tri gola prednosti|website=klix.ba|date=26 November 2024|access-date=27 November 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

In April 2025, he suffered a ruptured anterior cruciate ligament again and was predicted to miss at least half a year. He made his return to action over seven months after the injury, on 26 November.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n1info.ba/sport/nogomet/pobjednik-kola-lige-prvaka-za-navijace-iz-bih-sead-kolasinac-227-dana-kasnije|title=Pobjednik kola Lige prvaka za navijače iz BiH, Sead Kolašinac: 227 dana kasnije|website=n1info.ba|date=27 November 2025|access-date=27 November 2025|language=bs}}</ref>

He appeared in his 100th match for the team on 11 April 2026 against [[Juventus FC|Juventus]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/508576-sead-kolasinac-odigrao-100-utakmicu-u-dresu-atalante|title=Sead Kolašinac odigrao 100. utakmicu u dresu Atalante|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=11 April 2026|access-date=12 April 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

==International career==
Despite representing [[Germany national football team|Germany]] at various youth levels, Kolašinac decided to play for [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] at the senior level.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/bicakcic-i-kolasinac-srce-je-reklo-bosna-i-hercegovina/150915021|title=Bičakčić i Kolašinac: Srce je reklo Bosna i Hercegovina|website=klix.ba|date=15 September 2015|access-date=16 September 2015|language=bs}}</ref>

In November 2013, his request to change sports citizenship from German to Bosnian was approved by [[FIFA]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/sead-kolasinac-dobio-dozvolu-da-nastupa-za-bih/131107047|title=Sead Kolašinac dobio dozvolu da nastupa za BiH|website=klix.com|date=7 November 2013|access-date=7 November 2013|language=bs}}</ref> Later that month, he received his first senior call up, for a [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] game against [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/3776-safet-susic-pozvao-seada-kolasinca-za-utakmicu-protiv-argentine|title=Safet Sušić pozvao Seada Kolašinca za utakmicu protiv Argentine|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=7 November 2013|access-date=7 November 2013|language=bs}}</ref> and debuted in that match on 18 November.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/argentina-prejaka-za-zmajeve-aguero-poveo-gaucose-do-pobjede/132135|title=Argentina prejaka za Zmajeve, Agüero poveo Gaučose do pobjede|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=19 November 2013|access-date=22 November 2013|language=bs}}</ref>

In June 2014, Kolašinac was named in Bosnia and Herzegovina's squad for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]], country's first ever major competition.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://balkans.aljazeera.net/news/sports/2014/6/2/susic-objavio-konacan-spisak-za-brazil|title=Sušić objavio konačan spisak za Brazil|website=aljazeera.net|date=2 June 2014|access-date=5 June 2014|language=bs}}</ref> He made his tournament debut in the opening group tie against Argentina on 15 June.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/argentina-prejaka-ali-poslana-je-lijepa-slika-u-svijet/133674|title=Argentina prejaka, ali poslana je lijepa slika u svijet|website=sportsport.ba|date=16 June 2014|access-date=18 June 2014|language=bs}}</ref>

In May 2026, Kolašinac was selected for Bosnia and Herzegovina's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://fokus.ba/sport/reprezentacija/barbarez-objavio-spisak-ovih-26-igraca-ide-na-svjetsko-prvenstvo/3546757|title=Barbarez objavio spisak: Ovih 26 igrača ide na Svjetsko prvenstvo|website=fokus.ba|date=11 May 2026|access-date=11 May 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

==Style of play==
During his career, Kolašinac has been deployed as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre-back|centre-back]] and as a [[Midfielder#Defensive midfielder|defensive midfielder]], although he spent most of the time playing as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|left-back]]. He possesses very strong body build and strength.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/englezi-predstavili-bh-reprezentativca-sta-navijaci-arsenala-mogu-ocekivati-od-kolasinca/248638|title=Englezi predstavili bh. reprezentativca: Šta navijači Arsenala mogu očekivati od Kolašinca?|website=faktor.ba|date=15 May 2017|access-date=17 May 2017|language=bs}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Kolašinac married his long-time girlfriend Susubelle in June 2019. Together they have a daughter named Soleil.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://radiosarajevo.ba/sport/nogomet/sead-kolasinac-i-njegova-supruga-susubelle-postali-roditelji/387808|title=Sead Kolašinac i njegova supruga Susubelle postali roditelji|website=radiosarajevo.ba|date=26 August 2020|access-date=27 August 2020|language=bs}}</ref>

He is a practising [[Islam|Muslim]]; together with international teammates [[Ibrahim Šehić]], [[Muhamed Bešić]], [[Armin Hodžić (footballer, born 1994)|Armin Hodžić]], [[Izet Hajrović]], [[Edin Višća]] and [[Ervin Zukanović]] he visited a [[mosque]] in [[Zenica]] during the national team's concentration.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/zmajevi-u-zenickoj-dzamiji-klanjali-dzumu/336615|title=Zmajevi u zeničkoj džamiji klanjali džumu|website=sportsport.ba|date=11 October 2019|access-date=12 October 2019|language=bs}}</ref>

In July 2019, he and his then teammate [[Mesut Özil]] were victims of an attempted [[carjacking]], which Kolašinac successfully fought off.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/drama-u-londonu-ozila-napali-nozevima-spasio-ga-goloruki-kolasinac/190725150|title=Drama u Londonu: Özila napali noževima, spasio ga goloruki Kolašinac|website=klix.ba|date=25 July 2019|access-date=27 July 2019|language=bs}}</ref>

==Career statistics==

